<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 06 at 9:34PM MDT until July 06 at 10:15PM MDT by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Glasgow has issued a
* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
South central McCone County in northeastern Montana...
Central Prairie County in northeastern Montana...
Southwestern Dawson County in northeastern Montana...
* Until 1015 PM MDT.
* At 934 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 15 miles northwest
of Terry, moving east at 5 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.
* Locations impacted include...
Terry, Fallon and Mccloud.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
